data.title: Champ's Crown
data.prompt: Create a rap about winning a boxing championship
data.tags: gritty, hard-hitting, rap, boom-bap with heavy drums and sharp snares
data.lyrics:
[Verse]
Fists blazing, I’m a human meteor
Belt on my waist, I’m the new emperor
Canvas soaked, dreams drip in the ring
Each punch poetry, hear the leather sing

Blood on my gloves, sweat in my eyes
Opponents crumble, towers don’t rise
Crowd roars louder than a lion’s growl
Every swing a sermon, every hit a vow

[Chorus]
Champ’s crown, heavy but it’s mine now
Raised hands, bright lights, take a bow
Knockout dreams, built from the ground
They tried to stop me, but look at me now

[Verse 2]
Ropes my playground, dancing on the line
Footwork Picasso, masterpiece design
Opposition shaky, knees start to fold
Pressure in my veins, hotter than gold

Bell rings, my symphony’s composed
Left jab a comma, right hook the close
Sweat diamonds rain, flood the floor
Every fight a war, but I’m the victor for sure

[Bridge]
Felt the pain, the bruises, the weight
Pushed through the struggle, made my fate
Haters talked loud, but I silenced the sound
Now I’m the king, wearing the champ’s crown
